net.wequick.small

Class BundleLauncher

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.wequick.small.BundleLauncher
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ActivityLauncher, SoBundleLauncher

    public abstract class BundleLauncher
extends java.lang.Object
    This class resolve the bundle and launch it.

    In general the movement through a bundle launcher's lifecycle looks like this:

    Method Description Next
    setUp(Context) Called when the Small is setUp by Small.setUp(Context, Small.OnCompleteListener). This is where you should do all of your normal static set up: initialize the launcher, prepare for resolving bundle. preloadBundle(Bundle)
         preloadBundle(Bundle) Called when loading bundles by Bundle.loadLaunchableBundles(Small.OnCompleteListener). This is where you should do all of your normal validations and preparations. loadBundle(Bundle)
    loadBundle(Bundle) Called when the bundle is becoming resolvable to the launcher.

    Followed by preloadBundle(bundle) if the bundle is validated.

    		 nothing
         prelaunchBundle(Bundle) Called when the launcher will start an activity from the bundle. This is where you should do all of the intent build up: resolve the starting activity class, set the query parameters.

    Always followed by Small.openUri(uri, context).

    		 launchBundle(bundle)
    launchBundle(Bundle, Context) Called when the bundle is ready to launch. This is typically means the starting activity's intent has been prepared.

    Followed by prelaunchBundle(bundle).

    		 nothing

      • setUp

        public void setUp(android.content.Context context)
        Called when Small is setUp by Small.setUp(android.content.Context, net.wequick.small.Small.OnCompleteListener). This is where most initialization should go: initialize the launcher context, prepare for resolving bundle.
        Parameters:
        context - the context passed by Small.setUp(android.content.Context, net.wequick.small.Small.OnCompleteListener)

      • resolveBundle

        public boolean resolveBundle(Bundle bundle)
        Called when loading bundles by Bundle.loadLaunchableBundles(Small.OnCompleteListener).

        This method try to preload a bundle, if succeed, load it later.

        Parameters:
        bundle - the loading bundle
        Returns:
        true if the bundle is resolved

      • preloadBundle

        public boolean preloadBundle(Bundle bundle)
        Called when loading bundles by Bundle.loadLaunchableBundles(Small.OnCompleteListener). This is where validation and preparation should go: validate the bundle package name, validate the bundle signatures, record the bundle version for upgrade.
        Parameters:
        bundle - the loading bundle
        Returns:
        true if the bundle can be loaded

      • loadBundle

        public void loadBundle(Bundle bundle)
        Called after preloadBundle(Bundle) succeed. This is where most initialization should go: resolve the bundle activities or asset files, prepare the main entrance the bundle to start.
        Parameters:
        bundle - the loading bundle

      • prelaunchBundle

        public void prelaunchBundle(Bundle bundle)
        Called when launching a bundle by Small.openUri(java.lang.String, android.content.Context). This is where most initialization should go: prepare the intent of starting activity and passing parameters by the uri from Small.openUri(java.lang.String, android.content.Context).
        Parameters:
        bundle - the launching bundle

      • launchBundle

        public void launchBundle(Bundle bundle,
                android.content.Context context)
        Called after prelaunchBundle(Bundle). This is usually starting an activity.
        Parameters:
        bundle - the launching bundle
        context - current context

      • upgradeBundle

        public void upgradeBundle(Bundle bundle)
        Upgrade the bundle.

        This method should be called after you have downloaded the bundle's patch file witch code like downloadFile(url, bundle.getPatchFile());.

        Currently, we only set a flag in this method and do upgrading while the application launched at next time. TODO: Accomplish hotfix on application running.

        Parameters:
        bundle - the bundle to upgrade
